From: Dan Streetman <ddstreet@microsoft.com>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 15:22:40 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 10/11] fix(azurelinux): update hosts.azurelinux.tmpl (#6874)

Azure Linux 4.0 is Fedora-based, so update the hosts template to match
the fedora/redhat template.
---
 templates/hosts.azurelinux.tmpl | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/templates/hosts.azurelinux.tmpl b/templates/hosts.azurelinux.tmpl
index 8e3c23f6f..9e64e2691 100644
--- a/templates/hosts.azurelinux.tmpl
+++ b/templates/hosts.azurelinux.tmpl
@@ -19,4 +19,5 @@ you need to add the following to config:
 
 # The following lines are desirable for IPv6 capable hosts
 ::1 {{fqdn}} {{hostname}}
+::1 localhost.localdomain localhost
 ::1 localhost6.localdomain6 localhost6
